Sec. 2251.0031.  Exceptions for Certain Lines.   

(a)  Except as provided by Subsection (d), Subchapter C does not apply to any line of the 
following kinds of insurance written under a commercial insurance policy or contract issued by an 
insurer authorize d to engage in the business of insurance in this state:  
(1)  surety bonds;  
(2)  fidelity bonds;  
(3)  commercial inland marine;  
(4)  boiler and machinery;  
(5)  environmental impairment or pollution liability;  
(6)  kidnap and ransom;  
(7)  political risk or expropriation;  
